#1 login previous kernel version with good signature
#2 sudo mokutil --disable-validation
#3 enter regular password, e.g. 1 or TAOTAOzq_02
#4 input password to enter SecureBoot management
#5 sudo systemctl reboot
#6 enter into error kernel version's SecureBoot management by typing any key ...
#7 select menu to disable SecureBoot
#8 input password which is set in step #4
   note: the password input is very interesting, not the full password, but the nth character of the password
#9 disable SecureBoot
